    "The first is the perspective presented in section 2.3.2, where it is assumed that the semi-classical solutions [4,25] are exact and the worldsheet is in some way pinned to the boundary.",
    "In this picture, the meaningful dynamics are in the boundary directions since Φ → ∞.",
    "In this limit, the Wakimoto action (2.17) is replaced byS = - 1 4π d 2 z 4∂Φ ∂Φ + β∂γ + β ∂γ, (2.24)where the interaction term between Φ and β has negligible effect.",
    "17 In this picture, the worldsheet can only probe spacetime in the vicinity of the boundary and one concludes that it is only in this region in which physical perturbations occur (although there have been suggestions that in the limit of large spectral flow the interior can be probed [24,38]).",
